page.title: 16BIRDS
page.content: We went to the naze to see how many different kinds of birds we could find.We found 11 different birds and they were,a Swallow,Skylark,Black Headed Seagull,Meadow Pipit,Mistle Thrush,Kestrel,Wood Pigeon,Magpie, Swift,Male Linnet,Male Blackbird,Snow Bunting and a Common Gull.A lot of the time we were looking out for a Sparrowhawk which are quite common in this area but we did not see one.The most common bird we saw was the Wood Pigeon it is the largest Pigeon in the region and the most common Pigeon in Britain.
